      "writtenOn": "2021-01-27T09:26:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "P0: First, you are missing a noop test where CL patchset \u0026\u0026 trigger remain the same, but say a new message is posted.\n\nP2: Second, this \u0026 below tests are fragile: they\u0027ll work fine so long as impl. doesn\u0027t change substantially, but may continue passing if impl. changes with the reasons for cancelation differing from what test title says. This is the usual problem when one doesn\u0027t want to mock complete real world data and I had to accept such things in PM state tess, too. But, I think in this case, we can rectify this with the following setup:\n\n  ci :\u003d gf.CI(1, gf.PS(6), gf.CQ(+2))\n  tr :\u003d trigger.Find(ci)\n  cl :\u003d CL{1, Snapshot: {PS: 6, Gerrit: Info: ci }\n  rcl :\u003d RunCL{..., ci, tr}\n  Put(\u0026cl, \u0026rcl)\n  \n  Convey(\"most CL updates are noops\", {\n    // assert noop\n  })\n  Convey(\"Cancels Run on new Patchset\", {\n    ciV2 :\u003d gf.CI(1, gf.PS(7), gf.CQ(+2))\n    So(trigger.Find(ciV2), ShouldResembleProto, tr)\n    cl.Snapshot.PS \u003d 7\n    cl.Snapshot.Gerrit.Info \u003d ciV2\n    Put(\u0026cl)\n    // assert cancelled\n  })\n  Convey(\"Cancels Run on removed trigger\", {\n    ciV2 :\u003d gf.CI(1, gf.PS(6), gf.CQ(0))\n    So(trigger.Find(ciV2), ShouldBeNil)\n    cl.Snapshot.Gerrit.Info \u003d ciV2\n    Put(\u0026cl)\n    // assert cancelled\n  })\n\nWDYT?",
      "revId": "b2c54c6e82af4cb2632c1d7cf4107ad412724f43",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
